title: Egg - Wikipedia
snippet: An egg is an organic vessel grown by an animal to carry a possibly fertilized egg cell – a zygote. Within the vessel, an embryo is incubated until it has become an animal fetus that can survive on its own, at which point the animal hatches.

title: Eggs: Nutrition and Health Benefits
snippet: Dec 20, 2024 · Eggs are among the most nutritious foods on the planet. A whole egg contains all the nutrients required to turn a single cell into a baby chicken.
